addContact(string,string,uint256[]).details: Add a new contact to the address book

params._phoneNumbers: Array of phone numbers for the contact

returns.id: The ID of the newly created contact

deleteContact(uint256).details: Delete a contact from the address book

params._id: The ID of the contact to delete

getAllContacts().details: Get all contacts in the address book

params._id: The ID of the contact to retrieve

getContactCount().details: Get the total number of contacts

returns.count: The number of contacts in the address book

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
